* Usage

This program is used to create RGB colour codes for HTML documents. You can
change the red, green and blue components of the colour by moving the
scrollbars, or writing a number in the appropriate edit box. The HTML colour
code is displayed to the right of the colour sample box, and can be copied to
the clipboard by clicking on it. Clicking on the 'Quit' button will exit the
program.

* Command line parameters

The command line format of RGB is:

        rgb.exe [S|D|F|P|E] [-]

"S", "D", "F", "P" or "E" selects the language, S for Swedish, D for German, F
for French, P for Spanish or E for English, if the autodetection doesn't work
on your configuration. If used, this must always be the first parameter.

"-" makes RedGreenBlue always start centered on the screen (otherwise it will
read the coordinates used last time).

